From: Boldingh, Terry <Terry.Boldingh@bah.state.mn.us>
Sent: 5 Sep 2000 5:09 PM
Subject: Anthrax in Minnesota continues

Still having new cases of anthrax in Northern MN. 4th case was in Marshall
County about 40 miles South of the first Greenbush case. As of Saturday [2
Sep 2000 when I was at the farm, there were 3 dead cows. [The rest of the
herd was removed from pasture and vaccinated.
My guess is that the source was a site through a lowland area. The producer
used a field cultivator to remove ruts in a field path and disturbed the
soil????
Fifth case appears to be just South of the Canadian border about 6 miles
east of the RG case. 5 acute deaths but as yet no lab confirmation.
---
Terry Boldingh DVM
<terry.boldingh@bah.state.mn.us>
Tel: 218-643-2532

